- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing sentiment on Twitter, which is a social network platform. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper uses sentiment analysis techniques to analyze the data. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as the paper uses a dictionary-based sentiment analysis method. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper discusses the implications of its findings for public health applications. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) is another possible category as the paper examines how sentiment varies across different cities and time periods.
